The Commodity Credit Corporation,CCC, has accepted a bid for an export bonus to cover a sale of6,000 tonnes of semolina to Egypt, the U.S. AgricultureDepartment said.    The department said the semolina is for shipmentApril-October, 1987, and the bonus awarded was 224.87 dlrs pertonne.    The bonus was made to International Multifoods Corp andwill paid to the exporter in the form of commodities from CCCstocks, the department said.    An additional 7,000 tonnes of semolina are still availableto Egypt under the Export Enhancement Program initiativeannounced August 1, 1986, it said. Reuter&#3;